text: - My name is Jay Nguyen and I am part

of the Cloud Solutions Center
Account Management Team.
I have been at AWS for 2 1/2 years now.

I historically have been
in the tech sales industry
for the last five years.

AWS is a extremely
fast-growing organization

and their ability to
innovate for their customer

really caught my eye and
was interested in how
I can potentially bring value to customers
already utilizing AWS.
The biggest surprise at AWS

compared to my previous companies
was that AWS really cares
about transforming customers' businesses

and helping the customer
at the end of the day.
It's not so much about driving revenue,

but how to make things
right for the customer
and how to help the customer succeed.

I think professionally
it's great that I feel
like my peers are very collaborative.
They were always reaching out to me
seeing how they can help

and I think that's really
rubbed off on me as well
'cause now as someone that's been at AWS

for over two years now,
I reach out to newer reps

or individuals that just joined
AWS and kind of lead them

along the way as well,
which has been really,
I guess beneficial for the organization,

but has really helped me grown
as an individual as well.
(upbeat music)
